<HEADLINE>
FT  15 APR 92 / French keep tight grip on rate of inflation
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By IAN DAVIDSON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   PARIS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
FRENCH inflation remained stable in March, and significantly below the
average of its main trading partners, according to provisional figures
released by the National Statistical Institute.
The consumer price index rose 0.3 per cent in March, following similar
increases in February and January, and takes the year-on-year increase over
the past 12 months to 3.2 per cent.
The margin by which French inflation is undercutting that of Germany has
widened since the start of the year, and now stands at 1.5 percentage points
over the past 12 months.
This month the authorities expect a very slightly higher increase in the
consumer price index (up 0.4 per cent), but are forecasting a rate of
inflation for the year as a whole of only 2.8 per cent.
</TEXT>
