FT  14 APR 92 / Exchange contracts out IT operation
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW JACK
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE STOCK Exchange yesterday contracted out the management of its
information technology operations during the next five years to Andersen
Consulting and made 32 staff redundant, Andrew Jack writes.
Andersen will from today be wholly responsible for more than 300 remaining
IT staff and the equipment they run, which operates Stock Exchange systems
including the Seaq, Topic and Talisman information services.
Taurus, the new settlement system, is not included and a handful of IT staff
will remain to work on new development projects. Total employment has been
reduced from 1,900 to about 1,550 over the past few months, including
yesterday's action.
