<HEADLINE>
FT  14 APR 92 / Spanish inflation rises in March
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MADRID
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Spain's 0.4 per cent rise in the consumer price index (CPI) for March was
better than expected and could pave the way for easier interest rates but
the government will be hard-pressed to meet its 5 per cent target for the
year, economists said, Reuters reports from Madrid.
The March rise gave a year-on-year rise of 6.9 per cent, up on February's
6.8 per cent. Many analysts had expected this rate to accelerate to 7 per
cent with a month's rise of 0.5 to 0.7 per cent.
The figure was additionally positive because it included the annual
adjustment for government-controlled rents.
</TEXT>
