<HEADLINE>
FT  14 APR 92 / UK Company News: Touche Ross issues unmuddied facts about
Muddy Fox owners
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Touche Ross yesterday clarified the identity of the two new owners of Muddy
Fox, the privately-owned UK mountain bike company which came out of
administrative receivership earlier this month.
The UK accountant said it had been advised that the actual co-owners of
Muddy Fox are - as originally stated - Sitac, a UK-based engineering and
property group, and Parry Murray, and not TI Cycles of India as announced on
April 5.
Touche said Muruguppa Group of India had interests in both Tube Investments
of India (of which TI Cycles is part) and Parry Murray.
