circumstances - to the disadvantage of Germany's partners in the EC. This
slow response is an inevitable result of the coalition government which has
meant that, in a number of respects, Germany has failed to deal with long
standing issues. For example, with little privatisation in the former West
Germany, the German tax payer continues to pour huge sums of money into
